# Unity WebGL — TV Engine Rules

Unity-specific rules for TV games running as WebGL (WASM) in smart TV browsers. Requires `tv-platform-html5.mdc` alongside this file. For generic (non-Unity) WASM, see `tv-engine-wasm.mdc`.

The external shareable guide is in `external/tv-guide-unity-webgl.mdc`. This internal rule includes agent directives and proprietary thresholds.

---

## Architecture: what changes from native Unity

Unity WebGL compiles C# via **IL2CPP → C++ → Emscripten → WASM**. The JS files (`.framework.js`, `.loader.js`) are glue — game logic is WASM. No "compile to JS" option.

### Threading: limited, not absent

- **Engine threads** (physics, animation, audio, Burst jobs) parallelize on Chrome 92+ with COOP/COEP headers and `PlayerSettings.WebGL.threadsSupport`. See `tv-engine-wasm.mdc` for header details.
- **C# threads do NOT work** (`Task.Run`, `Thread`, `ThreadPool`). C# multithreading is "Under Consideration" on Unity roadmap. Game logic is single-threaded from C#.
- **Burst-compiled jobs** DO run on background threads when threading is enabled — the path to true parallelism.
- **Coroutines** and **async/await** (main thread) are the primary tools for spreading C# work across frames.

### No filesystem
`System.IO.File` does not work. Use `PlayerPrefs` (→ localStorage/IndexedDB) or custom `.jslib` → IndexedDB.

### Memory never shrinks
WASM heap grows but never returns to browser. Design around peak. Unload old assets before loading new. Pool everything.

### No native plugins
`.dll`/`.so` don't exist. Use `.jslib` for browser interop. `[DllImport("__Internal")]` for C# → JS calls.

### GC hits harder
Main-thread GC pauses = frame drops. No `new` in `Update()`. No LINQ in hot paths. Pool, pre-allocate, use structs. Enable incremental GC.

### Exceptions cost binary size
`Full with Stacktrace` doubles WASM size. Ship `Explicitly Thrown Exceptions Only`. Be defensive — check null, validate indices.

