## Build settings

| Setting | Value | Why |
|---------|-------|-----|
| Code Optimization | `Disk Size with LTO` | Smallest WASM binary |
| Strip Engine Code | Enabled | Remove unused engine modules |
| Managed Stripping Level | `High` | Strip unused C#. Test for reflection issues. |
| IL2CPP Code Generation | `Faster (Smaller) Builds` | Smaller output |
| Enable Exceptions | `Explicitly Thrown Exceptions Only` | Half the WASM size vs Full |
| Compression Format | `Brotli` | Best ratio. Requires HTTPS. |
| Decompression Fallback | `Disabled` | Avoid embedded JS decompressor |

WASM 2023 target: Chrome 91+. Use standard WASM if supporting Chrome 83-90.

---

## Memory configuration

| Setting | Low-end TV | High-end TV |
|---------|-----------|------------|
| Initial Memory Size | 64 MB | 128 MB |
| Maximum Memory Size | 256 MB | 384 MB |
| Memory Growth Mode | Geometric | Geometric |
| Geometric Growth Step | 0.2 (20%) | 0.2 |
| Growth Cap | 64 MB | 96 MB |

Total browser memory on low-end TV: 512 MB–1 GB shared with OS. WASM heap is separate from JS heap and GPU texture memory.

---

## Textures and assets

- **ETC2** default (ARM GPUs). ASTC for modern TVs only. **Never DXT** (software fallback).
- Reduce Max Size aggressively — 1024 or 512 for non-hero assets. Disable mipmaps for 2D/fixed-camera.
- **AssetBundles / Addressables** for non-first-screen content. LZ4 compression (LZMA not supported on WebGL). Server applies Brotli on top.
- **Initial download target: < 10 MB compressed** (WASM 3-6 MB + framework 0.5-1 MB + data 2-5 MB).
- Audio: Vorbis for music, ADPCM for SFX, 22,050 Hz sample rate.

---

## Input

- All input via DOM `keydown`/`keyup`. `WebGLInput.captureAllKeyboardInput = true`. `Cursor.visible = false`.
- **All UI navigable via D-pad + Enter + Back.** No mouse/touch. Visible focus state on everything.
- Unity UI Canvas: `Selectable` navigation (Explicit/Automatic). `StandaloneInputModule` responds to Submit + Cancel.
- Back keycode varies by platform — abstract via host page or `.jslib` integration.

---

## Loading and first paint

- **Custom WebGL template** (`Assets/WebGLTemplates/`). Inline splash in `index.html`. `onProgress` callback for progress bar.
- Hide splash only after Unity fully initialized and first frame rendered. Signal via `.jslib` callback.
- Use native **SplashScreen API** on Vega/Fire TV.
- **30 fps target** (33 ms budget). 60 fps possible on high-end with simple scenes. Set `Application.targetFrameRate` explicitly.

---

## Graphics

- Strip unused shader variants. Remove from Always Included Shaders.
- Simple shaders — TV GPUs (Mali, PowerVR) are slower than phone GPUs.
- No real-time shadows on low-end. Use baked lighting or blob shadows.
- Draw calls: **< 100** on low-end. Static batching, GPU instancing, texture atlases.
- FXAA (cheapest AA). No MSAA on TV GPUs.
- Render at 1920x1080 or 1280x720 upscaled if fill-rate bound.

---

## Lifecycle

- `visibilitychange` → `hidden`: pause (`Time.timeScale = 0`, `AudioListener.pause = true`). Audio bleed = cert failure.
- `visibilitychange` → `visible`: resume, re-check input.
- Save frequently via `PlayerPrefs` — OS can kill without warning.
- `.jslib` plugins for host page communication (splash hide, PAL info, analytics, Back button).

---

## Checklist

### Architecture
- [ ] Threading decision: Chrome 92+ only + no cross-origin resources → enable `threadsSupport` + COOP/COEP. Otherwise single-threaded C#.
- [ ] No `Task.Run()` / `Thread` / `ThreadPool` in C#. Coroutines, async/await (main thread), or Burst jobs.
- [ ] No `System.IO.File`. `PlayerPrefs` or `.jslib` → IndexedDB.
- [ ] Heavy C# chunked across frames. Burst jobs where possible.
- [ ] All native plugins have `.jslib` alternatives.
- [ ] No per-frame allocations. Pooling throughout.
- [ ] Level transitions: unload old before loading new.

### Build
- [ ] Release build (not Development). LTO. Brotli. High stripping. Explicitly Thrown exceptions.
- [ ] Incremental GC enabled.

### Assets
- [ ] ETC2 textures. Max sizes reduced. Unused shaders stripped.
- [ ] AssetBundles for non-first-screen. Initial download < 10 MB.
- [ ] Maximum Memory Size set.

### UX
- [ ] D-pad + Enter + Back navigable. Visible focus. Cursor hidden.
- [ ] Custom WebGL template with splash + progress.
- [ ] `visibilitychange` pauses audio/gameplay. Save often.

### Testing
- [ ] Real TV hardware at lowest tier. GC profiled. Peak WASM heap within ceiling.
